    "documentation": "# LINE Messenger\n\n## Overview\n\nThe LINE Messaging API allows developers to build rich conversational experiences on the LINE platform. Authentication is handled using **Channel Access Tokens**, which authorize your bot or application to interact with LINE users securely.\n\n## Authentication Ways\n\n- Channel Access Token\n\n## Channel Access Token\n\nTo authenticate with the LINE Messaging API, you need a Channel Access Token from your LINE Messaging API channel. This token authorizes API requests and links them to your specific bot.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Log in to LINE Business Console**  \n   - Go to <a href=\"https://developers.line.biz/console/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LINE Business Console</a> and log in using your LINE account.\n\n2. **Select Your Provider and Channel**  \n   - Choose your **Provider** and select the **Messaging API Channel** you want to use.\n\n3. **Get the Channel Access Token**  \n   - Navigate to the **Messaging API** tab  \n   - Under **Channel access token**, click **Issue** to generate or **Copy** to retrieve an existing token\n\nFor more details, visit the <a href=\"https://developers.line.biz/en/docs/messaging-api/overview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LINE Messaging API documentation</a>.",
